	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64590009">The Apollo-era suits worked as a system. Trying something radically different means that there would be a whole new range of problems. Just because someone claims "New and Improved!" doesn't mean it will be better. Improved may be better; new may be worse. There are human lives at stake--not just someone's bottom line. Lastly, some of the suit proposals, I see are just copies of Russian suits with ridged backs. If you study the Apollo program, you will see that Playtex's flexible suit design one, and won for a reason.</div>
	</div>

